Upgrade DjangoRestFramework
_____________________________

sudo pip install djangorestframework --upgrade


slumber
___________________
pip install slumber


GeoDjango - Django Geospatial libraries
___________________
sudo apt-get install binutils libproj-dev gdal-bin


#####

After you did the things below test Postgres SQL by setting in Django Settings:
'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.postgresql_psycopg2',

If that works, you want to setup postgis (plugin for geospatial operations directly in postgres) by setting in Django Settings:
'ENGINE': 'django.contrib.gis.db.backends.postgis',

!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Do not forget to delete the PORT in the DJANGO Settings, since Postgres uses a different port than mysql
!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
#####

